==English==
===Noun===
'''the [[straw]] [[that]] [[broke]] the [[camel]]'s [[back]]'''
#{{idiom}} A tiny addition to a [[burden]] that makes the entire thing hard to [[bear]]; that little thing which causes [[failure]].
#:''The whole project was difficult, but the extra steps imposed by the mandatory filing system were '''the straw that broke the camel's back'''.''

===Note===
The word ''straw'' here has the sense of a single piece of [[grass]] or [[hay]]; something very light weight.

===See also===
*[[the last straw]]

====Translations====
*Spanish: ser la [[gota]] que colma el [[vaso]] (ti be the drop that makes the glass to fall)